%I A395644 #8 May 06 2026 23:24:54
%S A395644 1,1,1,2,3,12,23,74,256,873,4151
%N A395644 Number of fibered prime knots with n crossings.
%C A395644 A knot is fibered if its complement in the 3-sphere fibers over the circle. Equivalently, a knot is fibered iff its Alexander polynomial is monic and its degree equals 2*g, where g is the three-genus.
%C A395644 Counts include all prime knots (alternating and non-alternating, rational and non-rational). The Perko duplicate (10_161 = 10_162) is excluded; counts are over distinct unoriented prime knots up to mirror image.
%C A395644 Fiberedness is a mirror-invariant property, so this count does not depend on chirality conventions.
%C A395644 Subsumes A051449 (rational fibered knots): every rational knot is prime, but not conversely. The sequences agree at c = 3, 4, 5, 6, 7 (all prime knots through c = 7 are rational) and diverge at c = 8 (A051449(8) = 4 fibered rational vs. 12 fibered prime).
%H A395644 KnotInfo, <a href="https://knotinfo.org/">Table of Knot Invariants</a>.
%H A395644 S. Oehms, <a href="https://github.com/soehms/database_knotinfo">database_knotinfo: KnotInfo and LinkInfo databases as Python package</a>, GitHub.
%H A395644 Alex Towell, <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19962842">Joint distributions of knot invariants for prime knots through 11 crossings</a>, Zenodo, 2026.
%e A395644 a(7) = 3: the 3 fibered prime knots with 7 crossings are 7_1, 7_6, 7_7. These are also the 3 fibered rational knots with 7 crossings (cf. A051449), since all prime knots with c <= 7 are rational.
%e A395644 a(8) = 12: of the 21 prime knots with 8 crossings, 12 are fibered. Of these, 4 are rational (cf. A051449(8) = 4) and 8 are not.
%Y A395644 Cf. A002863 (number of prime knots with n crossings).
%Y A395644 Cf. A051449 (number of fibered rational knots with n crossings).
%Y A395644 Cf. A002864 (alternating prime knots), A051763 (nonalternating prime knots).
%K A395644 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A395644 3,4
